<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="29" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.0011/9.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Penfield</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I regret to report assassination today at Sarajevo, Bosnia, of Archduke
                            Franz Ferdinand, heir apparent to the thrones of Austria-Hungary, and
                            his wife, the Duchess of Hohenberg, by pistol shots fired by a student.
                            The Archduke and wife were attending an official function. The Austrian
                            Emperor returns to Vienna Monday from Ischl.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>